  "texts": [
    "The American Medical Association recommends that written materials with health information for patients should be written at or below the 6th grade reading level 8.",
    "Linguistic Inquiry and Word Count (LIWC) text analysis software was used to analyze the textual characteristics of PLSs.",
    "Aside from the word count for each PLS, LIWC calculates the percentage of words in the PLSs that match different dictionary categories (Analytical tone, Clout, Authenticity and Emotional tone).",
    "The analytical tone variable indicates an objective writing style, with higher scores implying the text was written more formally, rationally and hierarchically.",
    "The clout variable is associated with confidence and assertiveness, with lower scores indicating a more hesitant text tone."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The American Medical Association recommends that written materials with health information for patients should be written at or below the 6th grade reading level 8."
  ]
}